  <brief_title>Study Of A Controlled Release Formulation Of Pregabalin In Fibromyalgia Patients</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Phase 3 Double-Blind, Randomized, Placebo-Controlled, Safety And Efficacy Study Of Once Daily Controlled Release Pregabalin In The Treatment Of Patients With Fibromyalgia (Protocol A0081245)</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Pfizer</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Pfizer</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the efficacy and safety of a controlled release
      formulation of pregabalin administered once daily as compared to placebo in the treatment of
      fibromyalgia. All patients will receive pregabalin; half of the patients will receive placebo
      at some point in the study.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
